<h1>Counting unique states in the SPPD Flock network</h1>

<h2>Method</h2>

<p>After normalizing all 602+ agency names and extracting state codes (step 2 of the pipeline), the script <code>count_states.py</code> deduplicates the extracted state codes and produces a list of unique states.</p>

<h2>Result</h2>

<p>44 unique states (plus D.C. if applicable from the original data). The full list is at <code>outputs/sppd-sharing-states/states.csv</code>.</p>

<h2>Caveats</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Agencies with no extractable state code (e.g., <code>"CSX Railroad"</code>, <code>"MAGLOCLEN RISS"</code>) are excluded from the state count.</li>
  <li>Full state names in agency names (e.g., <code>"Massachusetts Department of Correction"</code>) are converted to 2-letter codes.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Script</h2>

<p><code>analysis/count_states.py</code></p>